-= Kitchen =-
You've entered a typical room. Your mind races to think of what kind of room would be typical. And then it hits you. Of course. You're in the kitchen. You start to take note of what's in the room.

You can make out a fridge. The fridge contains a cilantro. You make out a closed oven, which looks conventional, close by. You can see a table. The table appears to be empty. Hm. Oh well You bend down to tie your shoe. When you stand up, you notice a counter. The counter is vast. On the counter you make out a cookbook. You can make out a stove. The stove is conventional.
